                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d804">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">704.1452/2: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Third Secretary of Embassy in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wendelin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-11-18T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 18, 1936—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>196. Your X–317, November 17, noon. We concur in your opinion that it would be
                    inadvisable to take charge of Guatemalan interests at this time. We have no
                    objection, however, to your giving shelter to the Chargé d’Affaires in the event
                    that he feels his personal safety endangered. You may also, in your discretion,
                    give refuge in the Embassy to such Guatemalan nationals as your facilities
                    permit.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
